items.definition: The School of Biological Sciences is based at the Clayton campus. It has research strengths in four discipline areas: Evolution, Genetics, Ecology and Conservation Biology.

items.definition: The Department of Civil Engineering is based at the Clayton campus, and was formed in 1961. It provides education and research outputs in the areas of: geomechanics, structures, transport, water and mining.

In late 1998, the Centre was relocated to new purpose-built premises on the Clayton campus.

items.definition: Defence Science and Technology Organisation's (DSTO) Maritime Division provides technologies and scientific and technical expertise to deliver the capability edge to the war fighter and enhance the operational performance and survivability of defence platforms in the maritime domain. In 2015, the DSTO changed its name to the Defence Science and Technology Group (DST Group).
